uratively] it is said to have in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "taEasa waA@notakasa", "text_ar": "تَعَسَ وَا@نْتَكَسَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", a form of imprecation, meaning, (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "May he be disappointed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fail, of attaining his desire:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for he who is overthrown in his affair ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "man A@notakasa fiY", "text_ar": "مَن ا@نْتَكَسَ فِى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^amorihi", "text_ar": "اَمْرِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") is disappointed of attaining his desire, and suffers loss. (TA.) [See also 1, where this form of imprecation is differently explained.] ―         -b2-  Also,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nak~asa raA^asahu", "text_ar": "نَكَّسَ رَاَسَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) [See 1, last signification.]"}], "source_refs": []}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}